Since \(V\) is nonnegative definite, we can write \(Q=Q_{1}Q_{2}\), where \(Q_{1}\) has orthonormal columns and \(Q_{2}\) is nonsingular. It follows that

\[Q_{2}^{-1}Q_{1}^{\prime}V=Q_{2}^{-1}Q_{1}^{\prime}[Q_{1}Q_{2}Q^{\prime}]=Q^{ \prime}.\]

